After coach Norma Plummer made a number of changes to the side that faced Jamaica, the Proteas edged the first quarter 14-10 as they eased their way into the match. Playing with real speed, the Proteas managed to extend their lead to 32-20 by half-time. The third and fourth quarter saw the Proteas dominate as they cruised to an easy victory. Lenize Potgieter managed a 100% shooting record on the night, converting all 30 of her attempts while Sigi Burger managed to slot 26 baskets out of her 29 attempts. The Proteas now play Uganda with a win securing them a semi-final spot. The match takes place on Wednesday at 20:00 (SA time).
